,"end":1775868893629}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775868893659,"sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","part":{"id":"prt_d7a08d9be001bDwRhGI134X1Ju","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a08b6d1001xQhyApnNch3ZMn","sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":21657,"input":4,"output":353,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":7160,"read":14140}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775868897351,"sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","part":{"id":"prt_d7a08e841001KkxgWLFhoVHptn","messageID":"msg_d7a08d9f70018hUXY2l7R7NcdV","sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868906251,"sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","part":{"id":"prt_d7a08f0cd001wCGXSzTclWviD5","messageID":"msg_d7a08d9f70018hUXY2l7R7NcdV","sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation) - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-014  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S  \n9: **Base Spec:** [AR-012: 会话存储接口定义](../AR-012/delta-spec.md)\n10: \n11: The Valkey Storage Implementation provides a concrete implementation of the Store interface using Valkey as the backend. Valkey is a Redis-compatible storage engine, and this AR leverages the `valkey-go` client library to provide CRUD operations on sandbox information with sorted set indexes for expiry and last activity times.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Valkey Store Implementation\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a Valkey-backed Store implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` that satisfies the Store interface.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Valkey Ping returns PONG\n22: - **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server at `VALKEY_ADDR`\n23: - **AND** a valid `valkeyStore` instance\n24: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n25: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `PING` command\n26: - **AND** require string response `PONG`\n27: - **AND** return `nil` error on success\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: Valkey Ping fails on connection error\n30: - **GIVEN** an unreachable Valkey server\n31: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n32: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n33: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox\n36: - **GIVEN** a session exists with key `session:abc123` containing valid JSON\n37: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n38: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n39: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `GET session:abc123`\n40: - **AND** return the unmarshaled `*types.SandboxInfo`\n41: - **AND** return `nil` error\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns ErrNotFound for missing key\n44: - **GIVEN** no key `session:abc123` exists in Valkey\n45: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n46: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n47: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect nil/empty result\n48: - **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n51: - **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n52: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n53: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n54: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n55: - **AND** SHALL NOT query Valkey\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates input\n58: - **GIVEN** a nil sandbox pointer\n59: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n60: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n61: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n62: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates SessionID\n65: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n66: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n67: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n68: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n69: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates ExpiresAt\n72: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n73: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n74: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n75: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating expiresAt is zero\n76: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox uses atomic pipeline\n79: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Now().Add(time.Hour)`\n80: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n81: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n82: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a pipeline:\n83:   - `SETNX session:sess-1 {json}`\n84:   - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} sess-1`\n85:   - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} sess-1`\n86: - **AND** all commands SHALL succeed\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox fails if session already exists\n89: - **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` already exists\n90: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n91: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called with same SessionID\n92: - **THEN** `SETNX` SHALL indicate key exists\n93: - **AND** the implementation SHALL return error indicating session already exists\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox requires existing key\n96: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n97: - **AND** key `session:sess-1` does NOT exist in Valkey\n98: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n99: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n100: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n101: - **AND** return `ErrNotFound` if key does not exist\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox succeeds for existing key\n104: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n105: - **AND** key `session:sess-1` exists in Valkey\n106: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n107: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n108: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n109: - **AND** update the JSON value\n110: - **AND** return `nil` error\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes session and indexes\n113: - **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` exists\n114: - **AND** `session:expiry` has member `sess-1`\n115: - **AND** `session:last_activity` has member `sess-1`\n116: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n117: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n118: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a pipeline:\n119:   - `DEL session:sess-1`\n120:   - `ZREM session:expiry sess-1`\n121:   - `ZREM session:last_activity sess-1`\n122: - **AND** return `nil` error on success\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID returns error for missing key\n125: - **GIVEN** no key `session:sess-1` exists\n126: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n127: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n128: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect no key was deleted\n129: - **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired sessions\n132: - **GIVEN** `session:expiry` ZSET contains entries with scores (timestamps)\n133: - **AND** some entries have scores less than or equal to `before` timestamp\n134: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n135: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n136: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry 0 {before} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n137: - **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo` for each session found\n138: - **AND** return results ordered by expiry time (ascending)\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes returns inactive sessions\n141: - **GIVEN** `session:last_activity` ZSET contains entries with scores (timestamps)\n142: - **AND** some entries have scores less than or equal to `before` timestamp\n143: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n144: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n145: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity 0 {before} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n146: - **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo` for each session found\n147: - **AND** return results ordered by last activity time (ascending)\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity updates ZSET\n150: - **GIVEN** a session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` exists\n151: - **AND** current time is `now`\n152: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n153: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", now)` is called\n154: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZADD session:last_activity {now.Unix()} sess-1`\n155: - **AND** return `nil` error on success\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Valkey Close releases connections\n158: - **GIVEN** a `valkeyStore` instance with active connections\n159: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n160: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL close the Valkey client\n161: - **AND** release all connection resources\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## Configuration\n166: \n167: ### Environment Variables\n168: \n169: | Variable | Description | Default |\n170: |----------|-------------|---------|\n171: | `STORE_TYPE` | Storage backend type (valkey) | - |\n172: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Valkey server address | `localhost:6379` |\n173: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Valkey authentication password | - |\n174: | `VALKEY_DB` | Valkey database number | `0` |\n175: | `VALKEY_POOL_SIZE` | Connection pool size | `10` |\n176: | `VALKEY_MIN_IDLE_CONNS` | Minimum idle connections | `5` |\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ## Dependencies\n181: \n182: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` - Valkey Go client\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## Notes\n187: \n188: - Valkey is Redis-compatible, so the command patterns mirror AR-013\n189: - The valkey-go client uses a different API pattern compared to go-redis/v9\n190: - Pipeline/Multi operations should be implemented using valkey-go's DoMulti\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-014  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Base Spec:** [AR-012: 会话存储接口定义](../AR-012/delta-spec.md)\n\nThe Valkey Storage Implementation provides a concrete implementation of the Store interface using Valkey as the backend. Valkey is a Redis-compatible storage engine, and this AR leverages the `valkey-go` client library to provide CRUD operations on sandbox information with sorted set indexes for expiry and last activity times.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Valkey Store Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Valkey-backed Store implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` that satisfies the Store interface.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775868906215,"end":1775868906249}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868906252,"sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","part":{"id":"prt_d7a08f68b001hUWjB8vi5HFruY","messageID":"msg_d7a08d9f70018hUXY2l7R7NcdV","sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/valkey.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/valkey.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package store\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \t\"context\"\n21: \t\"encoding/json\"\n22: \t\"fmt\"\n23: \t\"time\"\n24: \n25: \t\"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n26: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n27: )\n28: \n29: // valkeyStore implements Store interface using Valkey backend.\n30: type valkeyStore struct {\n31: \tcli                  valkey.Client\n32: \tsessionPrefix        string\n33: \texpiryIndexKey       string\n34: \tlastActivityIndexKey string\n35: }\n36: \n37: // newValkeyStore creates a new Valkey-backed Store instance.\n38: func newValkeyStore() (Store, error) {\n39: \topts, err := makeValkeyOptions()\n40: \tif err != nil {\n41: \t\treturn nil, err\n42: \t}\n43: \n44: \tclientOption := valkey.ClientOption{\n45: \t\tInitAddress:       opts.InitAddress,\n46: \t\tDisableCache:      opts.DisableCache,\n47: \t\tForceSingleClient: opts.ForceSingleClient,\n48: \t}\n49: \n50: \t// Configure password if provided\n51: \tif opts.Password != \"\" {\n52: \t\tclientOption.Password = opts.Password\n53: \t}\n54: \n55: \tclient, err := valkey.NewClient(clientOption)\n56: \tif err != nil {\n57: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create valkey client: %w\", err)\n58: \t}\n59: \n60: \treturn &valkeyStore{\n61: \t\tcli:                  client,\n62: \t\tsessionPrefix:        sessionPrefix,\n63: \t\texpiryIndexKey:       expiryIndexKey,\n64: \t\tlastActivityIndexKey: lastActivityIndexKey,\n65: \t}, nil\n66: }\n67: \n68: // sessionKey constructs the Valkey key for a session.\n69: func (s *valkeyStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n70: \treturn s.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n71: }\n72: \n73: // Ping verifies connectivity to the Valkey backend.\n74: // Returns nil on success, error on failure.\n75: func (s *valkeyStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n76: \tresult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Ping().Build())\n77: \tif result.Error() != nil {\n78: \t\treturn result.Error()\n79: \t}\n80: \n81: \tpong, err := result.ToString()\n82: \tif err != nil {\n83: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse ping response: %w\", err)\n84: \t}\n85: \tif pong != \"PONG\" {\n86: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected ping response: %s\", pong)\n87: \t}\n88: \treturn nil\n89: }\n90: \n91: // GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves sandbox info by session ID.\n92: // Returns ErrNotFound if the session does not exist.\n93: func (s *valkeyStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n94: \tif sessionID == \"\" {\n95: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"sessionID is empty\")\n96: \t}\n97: \n98: \tkey := s.sessionKey(sessionID)\n99: \tresult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Get().Key(key).Build())\n100: \tif result.Error() != nil {\n101: \t\tif valkey.IsValkeyNil(result.Error()) {\n102: \t\t\treturn nil, ErrNotFound\n103: \t\t}\n104: \t\treturn nil, result.Error()\n105: \t}\n106: \n107: \tdata, err := result.ToString()\n108: \tif err != nil {\n109: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get session data: %w\", err)\n110: \t}\n111: \n112: \tvar sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n113: \tif err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &sandbox); err != nil {\n114: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n115: \t}\n116: \n117: \treturn &sandbox, nil\n118: }\n119: \n120: // StoreSandbox creates a new sandbox entry with atomic index updates.\n121: // Validates sandbox is non-nil and has valid ExpiresAt.\n122: // Uses SETNX to prevent overwriting existing keys.\n123: func (s *valkeyStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n124: \tif sandbox == nil {\n125: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox is nil\")\n126: \t}\n127: \tif sandbox.SessionID == \"\" {\n128: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sessionID is empty\")\n129: \t}\n130: \tif sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n131: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"expiresAt is zero\")\n132: \t}\n133: \n134: \tkey := s.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n135: \tdata, err := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n136: \tif err != nil {\n137: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n138: \t}\n139: \n140: \tnow := time.Now().Unix()\n141: \n142: \t// Use DoMulti for atomic operations\n143: \tresults := s.cli.DoMulti(ctx,\n144: \t\ts.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Nx().Build(),\n145: \t\ts.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).ScoreMember().\n146: \t\t\tScoreMember(float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix()), sandbox.SessionID).Build(),\n147: \t\ts.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().\n148: \t\t\tScoreMember(float64(now), sandbox.SessionID).Build(),\n149: \t)\n150: \n151: \t// Check for errors in any of the results\n152: \tfor i, r := range results {\n153: \t\tif r.Error() != nil {\n154: \t\t\t// Clean up already executed commands on error (best effort)\n155: \t\t\treturn r.Error()\n156: \t\t}\n157: \n158: \t\t// First command is SET NX - check if it succeeded\n159: \t\tif i == 0 {\n160: \t\t\tsetResult, err := r.ToString()\n161: \t\t\tif err != nil {\n162: \t\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"session already exists\")\n163: \t\t\t}\n164: \t\t\tif setResult != \"OK\" {\n165: \t\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"session already exists\")\n166: \t\t\t}\n167: \t\t}\n168: \t}\n169: \n170: \treturn nil\n171: }\n172: \n173: // UpdateSandbox updates an existing sandbox's JSON data.\n174: // Uses SET with XX flag (key must exist).\n175: // Does NOT modify expiry or last-activity indexes.\n176: func (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n177: \tif sandbox == nil {\n178: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox is nil\")\n179: \t}\n180: \tif sandbox.SessionID == \"\" {\n181: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sessionID is empty\")\n182: \t}\n183: \n184: \tkey := s.sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)\n185: \tdata, err := json.Marshal(sandbox)\n186: \tif err != nil {\n187: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n188: \t}\n189: \n190: \t// SET with XX flag - only set if key exists\n191: \tresult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Xx().Build())\n192: \tif result.Error() != nil {\n193: \t\treturn result.Error()\n194: \t}\n195: \n196: \t// Check if the operation succeeded (XX returns nil/empty if key doesn't exist)\n197: \tstrResult, err := result.ToString()\n198: \tif err != nil {\n199: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists\")\n200: \t}\n201: \tif strResult != \"OK\" {\n202: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"key not exists\")\n203: \t}\n204: \n205: \treturn nil\n206: }\n207: \n208: // DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes a sandbox and its indexes.\n209: // Uses atomic pipeline: DEL + ZREM expiry + ZREM last_activity.\n210: func (s *valkeyStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n211: \tif sessionID == \"\" {\n212: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sessionID is empty\")\n213: \t}\n214: \n215: \tkey := s.sessionKey(sessionID)\n216: \n217: \t// Use DoMulti for atomic operations\n218: \tresults := s.cli.DoMulti(ctx,\n219: \t\ts.cli.B().Del().Key(key).Build(),\n220: \t\ts.cli.B().Zrem().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n221: \t\ts.cli.B().Zrem().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build(),\n222: \t)\n223: \n224: \t// Check for errors\n225: \tfor _, r := range results {\n226: \t\tif r.Error() != nil {\n227: \t\t\treturn r.Error()\n228: \t\t}\n229: \t}\n230: \n231: \treturn nil\n232: }\n233: \n234: // ListExpiredSandboxes returns sessions with ExpiresAt <= before.\n235: // Queries session:expiry ZSET with ZRANGEBYSCORE.\n236: // Returns nil, nil if limit <= 0.\n237: func (s *valkeyStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n238: \tif limit <= 0 {\n239: \t\treturn nil, nil\n240: \t}\n241: \n242: \t// Get expired session IDs from the ZSET\n243: \tzrangeResult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).\n244: \t\tMin(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).Limit(0, limit).Build())\n245: \tif zrangeResult.Error() != nil {\n246: \t\treturn nil, zrangeResult.Error()\n247: \t}\n248: \n249: \tarr, err := zrangeResult.ToArray()\n250: \tif err != nil {\n251: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse zrange result: %w\", err)\n252: \t}\n253: \n254: \tsessionIDs := make([]string, 0, len(arr))\n255: \tfor _, v := range arr {\n256: \t\tid, err := v.ToString()\n257: \t\tif err != nil {\n258: \t\t\tcontinue\n259: \t\t}\n260: \t\tsessionIDs = append(sessionIDs, id)\n261: \t}\n262: \n263: \treturn s.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n264: }\n265: \n266: // ListInactiveSandboxes returns sessions with last activity <= before.\n267: // Queries session:last_activity ZSET with ZRANGEBYSCORE.\n268: // Returns nil, nil if limit <= 0.\n269: func (s *valkeyStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n270: \tif limit <= 0 {\n271: \t\treturn nil, nil\n272: \t}\n273: \n274: \t// Get inactive session IDs from the ZSET\n275: \tzrangeResult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Zrangebyscore().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).\n276: \t\tMin(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).Limit(0, limit).Build())\n277: \tif zrangeResult.Error() != nil {\n278: \t\treturn nil, zrangeResult.Error()\n279: \t}\n280: \n281: \tarr, err := zrangeResult.ToArray()\n282: \tif err != nil {\n283: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse zrange result: %w\", err)\n284: \t}\n285: \n286: \tsessionIDs := make([]string, 0, len(arr))\n287: \tfor _, v := range arr {\n288: \t\tid, err := v.ToString()\n289: \t\tif err != nil {\n290: \t\t\tcontinue\n291: \t\t}\n292: \t\tsessionIDs = append(sessionIDs, id)\n293: \t}\n294: \n295: \treturn s.loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)\n296: }\n297: \n298: // loadSandboxesBySessionIDs loads sandbox info for the given session IDs.\n299: // Skips entries where the session key is missing (orphaned ZSET entries).\n300: func (s *valkeyStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, sessionIDs []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n301: \tif len(sessionIDs) == 0 {\n302: \t\treturn []*types.SandboxInfo{}, nil\n303: \t}\n304: \n305: \t// Build keys for all session IDs\n306: \tkeys := make([]string, len(sessionIDs))\n307: \tfor i, id := range sessionIDs {\n308: \t\tkeys[i] = s.sessionKey(id)\n309: \t}\n310: \n311: \t// Use MGET to fetch all sessions in one call\n312: \tmgetResult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build())\n313: \tif mgetResult.Error() != nil {\n314: \t\treturn nil, mgetResult.Error()\n315: \t}\n316: \n317: \tarr, err := mgetResult.ToArray()\n318: \tif err != nil {\n319: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse mget result: %w\", err)\n320: \t}\n321: \n322: \t// Parse results, skipping empty entries (orphaned ZSET members)\n323: \tsandboxes := make([]*types.SandboxInfo, 0, len(arr))\n324: \tfor _, v := range arr {\n325: \t\tdata, err := v.ToString()\n326: \t\tif err != nil {\n327: \t\t\t// Nil value or error - skip\n328: \t\t\tcontinue\n329: \t\t}\n330: \n331: \t\tif data == \"\" {\n332: \t\t\t// Orphaned ZSET entry - skip\n333: \t\t\tcontinue\n334: \t\t}\n335: \n336: \t\tvar sandbox types.SandboxInfo\n337: \t\tif err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &sandbox); err != nil {\n338: \t\t\t// Failed to parse - skip this entry but continue\n339: \t\t\tcontinue\n340: \t\t}\n341: \n342: \t\tsandboxes = append(sandboxes, &sandbox)\n343: \t}\n344: \n345: \treturn sandboxes, nil\n346: }\n347: \n348: // UpdateSessionLastActivity updates the last activity timestamp for a session.\n349: // Returns ErrNotFound if session does not exist.\n350: // If at is zero time, uses time.Now().\n351: func (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n352: \tif sessionID == \"\" {\n353: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"sessionID is empty\")\n354: \t}\n355: \n356: \t// Verify session exists before updating\n357: \tkey := s.sessionKey(sessionID)\n358: \texistsResult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Exists().Key(key).Build())\n359: \tif existsResult.Error() != nil {\n360: \t\treturn existsResult.Error()\n361: \t}\n362: \n363: \texists, err := existsResult.ToInt64()\n364: \tif err != nil {\n365: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"failed to check session existence: %w\", err)\n366: \t}\n367: \tif exists == 0 {\n368: \t\treturn ErrNotFound\n369: \t}\n370: \n371: \t// Use current time if at is zero\n372: \tif at.IsZero() {\n373: \t\tat = time.Now()\n374: \t}\n375: \n376: \t// Update the activity index\n377: \tzaddResult := s.cli.Do(ctx, s.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().\n378: \t\tScoreMember(float64(at.Unix()), sessionID).Build())\n379: \tif zaddResult.Error() != nil {\n380: \t\treturn zaddResult.Error()\n381: \t}\n382: \n383: \treturn nil\n384: }\n385: \n386: // Close closes the Valkey connection.\n387: func (s *valkeyStore) Close() error {\n388: \ts.cli.Close()\n389: \treturn nil\n390: }\n\n(End of file - total 390 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage store\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/valkey.go","time":{"start":1775868906219,"end":1775868906251}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868906254,"sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0900b2001dKBKkIBtoRld2o","messageID":"msg_d7a08d9f70018hUXY2l7R7NcdV","sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/store.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/store.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package store\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \t\"context\"\n21: \t\"errors\"\n22: \t\"time\"\n23: \n24: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n25: )\n26: \n27: // ErrNotFound is returned when a session is not found in the store.\n28: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n29: \n30: // Store defines the interface for session storage backends.\n31: // Implementations include Redis and Valkey providers.\n32: type Store interface {\n33: \t// Ping checks connectivity to the store.\n34: \tPing(ctx context.Context) error\n35: \n36: \t// GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves sandbox information by session ID.\n37: \t// Returns ErrNotFound if the session does not exist.\n38: \tGetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n39: \n40: \t// StoreSandbox stores sandbox information in the store.\n41: \tStoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n42: \n43: \t// UpdateSandbox updates existing sandbox information.\n44: \tUpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n45: \n46: \t// DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes a sandbox from the store.\n47: \tDeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n48: \n49: \t// ListExpiredSandboxes returns sandboxes that have expired before the given time.\n50: \tListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n51: \n52: \t// ListInactiveSandboxes returns sandboxes inactive since before the given time.\n53: \tListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n54: \n55: \t// UpdateSessionLastActivity updates the last activity timestamp for a session.\n56: \tUpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n57: \n58: \t// Close closes the store connection.\n59: \tClose() error\n60: }\n\n(End of file - total 60 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage store\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pk