{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869081290,"sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","part":{"id":"prt_d7a099edc001nCsY3L6M5WCUwL","messageID":"msg_d7a095979001g25J367rjadqEi","sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-014  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Base Spec:** [session-store/spec.md](../../session-store/spec.md)\n\nThe Valkey Storage Implementation provides a concrete Store implementation using Valkey as the backend. Valkey is a Redis-compatible storage engine, and this AR leverages the `valkey-go` client library to provide CRUD operations on sandbox information with sorted set indexes for expiry and last activity times.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Valkey Store Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Valkey-backed Store implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` that satisfies the Store interface.\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey Ping returns PONG\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server at `VALKEY_ADDR`\n- **AND** a valid `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `PING` command using `B().Ping().Build()`\n- **AND** require string response `PONG`\n- **AND** return `nil` error on success\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey Ping fails on connection error\n- **GIVEN** an unreachable Valkey server\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a session exists with key `session:abc123` containing valid JSON\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `GET session:abc123` using `B().Get().Key(key).Build()`\n- **AND** return the unmarshaled `*types.SandboxInfo`\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns ErrNotFound for missing key\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:abc123` exists in Valkey\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect `valkey.IsValkeyNil(result.Error())` as true\n- **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n- **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT query Valkey\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates input\n- **GIVEN** a nil sandbox pointer\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates SessionID\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates ExpiresAt\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating expiresAt is zero\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox uses atomic DoMulti\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Now().Add(time.Hour)`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a single `DoMulti` call:\n  - `SETNX session:sess-1 {json}` using `B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Nx().Build()`\n  - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} sess-1` using `B().Zadd().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix()), sandbox.SessionID).Build()`\n  - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} sess-1` using `B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(now), sandbox.SessionID).Build()`\n- **AND** all commands SHALL succeed for the operation to complete\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox fails if session already exists\n- **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` already exists\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called with same SessionID\n- **THEN** `SETNX` SHALL indicate key exists (return value other than \"OK\")\n- **AND** the implementation SHALL return error indicating session already exists\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox requires existing key\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** key `session:sess-1` does NOT exist in Valkey\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX` using `B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Xx().Build()`\n- **AND** return error indicating \"key not exists\" if key does not exist (result not \"OK\")\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox succeeds for existing key\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** key `session:sess-1` exists in Valkey\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n- **AND** update the JSON value\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes session and indexes\n- **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` exists\n- **AND** `session:expiry` has member `sess-1`\n- **AND** `session:last_activity` has member `sess-1`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a single `DoMulti` call:\n  - `DEL session:sess-1` using `B().Del().Key(key).Build()`\n  - `ZREM session:expiry sess-1` using `B().Zrem().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n  - `ZREM session:last_activity sess-1` using `B().Zrem().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n- **AND** return `nil` error on success\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired sessions\n- **GIVEN** `session:expiry` ZSET contains entries with scores (timestamps)\n- **AND** some entries have scores less than or equal to `before` timestamp\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called with limit > 0\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()}` using `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).Limit(0, limit).Build()`\n- **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo` for each session found\n- **AND** return results ordered by expiry time (ascending)\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n- **GIVEN** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)` or negative limit is called\n- **THEN** return `nil, nil` without querying Valkey\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes returns inactive sessions\n- **GIVEN** `session:last_activity` ZSET contains entries with scores (timestamps)\n- **AND** some entries have scores less than or equal to `before` timestamp\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called with limit > 0\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix()}` using `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).Limit(0, limit).Build()`\n- **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo` for each session found\n- **AND** return results ordered by last activity time (ascending)\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n- **GIVEN** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)` or negative limit is called\n- **THEN** return `nil, nil` without querying Valkey\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity updates ZSET\n- **GIVEN** a session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` exists\n- **AND** current time is `now`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", now)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL first verify key exists using `B().Exists().Key(key).Build()`\n- **AND** if exists returns 1, execute `ZADD session:last_activity {now.Unix()} sess-1` using `B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(at.Unix()), sessionID).Build()`\n- **AND** return `nil` error on success\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity returns ErrNotFound for missing session\n- **GIVEN** no session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` exists\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", now)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL verify key exists using `B().Exists().Key(key).Build()`\n- **AND** when exists returns 0, return `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity uses current time when at is zero\n- **GIVEN** a session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` exists\n- **AND** zero time `time.Time{}` is passed as `at` parameter\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", time.Time{})` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL use `time.Now()` as the activity timestamp\n- **AND** execute `ZADD session:last_activity {now.Unix()} sess-1`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey Close releases connections\n- **GIVEN** a `valkeyStore` instance with active connections\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL call `s.cli.Close()`\n- **AND** return `nil`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey loadSandboxesBySessionIDs tolerates orphaned entries\n- **GIVEN** a list of session IDs from ZSET query including orphaned entries (no corresponding session key)\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL use `MGET` with all session keys using `B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build()`\n- **AND** skip entries where `v.ToString()` returns error or empty string\n- **AND** return only valid sandbox entries without error\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Valkey Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL read Valkey configuration from environment variables and create appropriate client options.\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ADDR is required\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is not set\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n- **THEN** return error indicating `VALKEY_ADDR is required`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ADDR supports multiple addresses\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=\"host1:6379,host2:6379,host3:6379\"`\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n- **THEN** return `InitAddress` as `[]string{\"host1:6379\", \"host2:6379\", \"host3:6379\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not set\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n- **THEN** return error indicating `VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey password can be disabled\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty\n- **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n- **THEN** return options with empty password and no error\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey DisableCache option\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n- **THEN** return options with `DisableCache: true`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ForceSingleClient option\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n- **THEN** return options with `ForceSingleClient: true`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey password parsing is case-insensitive for REQUIRED\n- **GIVEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=FALSE` or `False` or `false`\n- **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n- **THEN** treat as password not required\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Provider Selection\n\nThe system SHALL support runtime selection between Redis and Valkey backends via `STORE_TYPE` environment variable.\n\n#### Scenario: Default to Redis when STORE_TYPE is unset\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` environment variable is not set\n- **WHEN** `initStore()` is called\n- **THEN** default store type is `redis`\n\n#### Scenario: Select Valkey when STORE_TYPE=valkey\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey` (case-insensitive)\n- **WHEN** `initStore()` is called\n- **THEN** create and return `valkeyStore` instance\n\n#### Scenario: Reject unsupported store type\n- **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=unsupported`\n- **WHEN** `initStore()` is called\n- **THEN** return error indicating `unsupported store type: unsupported (supported: redis, valkey)`\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Storage backend type (`redis` or `valkey`) |\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated list of Valkey server addresses |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | - | Valkey authentication password |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to allow empty password |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client-side caching |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to force single client mode |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` - Valkey Go client (v1.0.0+)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Valkey is Redis-compatible, so the command patterns mirror Redis implementation\n- The `valkey-go` client uses a builder pattern (`B()`) for constructing commands\n- Pipeline/Multi operations use `DoMulti()` for atomic execution\n- Nil checks use `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` instead of `redis.Nil`\n- String results use `result.ToString()` instead of direct string conversion\n- Array results from `ZRANGEBYSCORE` use `result.ToArray()` then iterate with `v.ToString()`\n- MGET results use `result.ToArray()` and skip entries where `ToString()` returns error\n- All ZSET scores use Unix timestamp (seconds since epoch) as float64\n\n---\n\n## Key Differences from Redis Implementation\n\n| Aspect | Redis (go-redis/v9) | Valkey (valkey-go) |\n|--------|---------------------|-------------------|\n| Client creation | `redis.NewClient(opts)` | `valkey.NewClient(opt)` |\n| Command building | Direct methods | Builder pattern `B().Cmd().Build()` |\n| Pipelines | `Pipeline()` + `Exec()` | `DoMulti()` |\n| Nil check | `err == redis.Nil` | `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` |\n| Get result | `.Result()` string | `.ToString()` on result |\n| Array result | Direct slice | `.ToArray()` then `.ToString()` |\n| Close | Returns error | Returns nil |\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/redis.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/singleton.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/store.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/valkey.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":18,"character":42},"end":{"line":18,"character":53}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 should be direct"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/common/types/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/redis_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":38,"character":26},"end":{"line":38,"character":38}},"severity":3,"code":"unusedparams","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedparams#unusedparams"},"source":"unusedparams","message":"unused parameter: t"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/store_test.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775869081257,"end":1775869081286}}}}
