{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869093691,"sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0be228001D8SNoK19P1r5lC","messageID":"msg_d7a0bd3da001daTH3LJx2Mv29f","sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:16","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-014  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S  \n9: **Base Spec:** [session-store/spec.md](../../session-store/spec.md)\n10: \n11: The Valkey Storage Implementation provides a concrete Store implementation using Valkey as the backend. Valkey is a Redis-compatible storage engine, and this AR leverages the `valkey-go` client library to provide CRUD operations on sandbox information with sorted set indexes for expiry and last activity times.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Valkey Store Implementation\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a Valkey-backed Store implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` that satisfies the Store interface.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Valkey Ping returns PONG\n22: - **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server at `VALKEY_ADDR`\n23: - **AND** a valid `valkeyStore` instance\n24: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n25: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `PING` command using `B().Ping().Build()`\n26: - **AND** require string response `PONG`\n27: - **AND** return `nil` error on success\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: Valkey Ping fails on connection error\n30: - **GIVEN** an unreachable Valkey server\n31: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n32: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n33: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox\n36: - **GIVEN** a session exists with key `session:abc123` containing valid JSON\n37: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n38: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n39: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `GET session:abc123` using `B().Get().Key(key).Build()`\n40: - **AND** return the unmarshaled `*types.SandboxInfo`\n41: - **AND** return `nil` error\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns ErrNotFound for missing key\n44: - **GIVEN** no key `session:abc123` exists in Valkey\n45: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n46: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n47: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect `valkey.IsValkeyNil(result.Error())` as true\n48: - **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n51: - **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n52: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n53: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n54: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n55: - **AND** SHALL NOT query Valkey\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates input\n58: - **GIVEN** a nil sandbox pointer\n59: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n60: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n61: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n62: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates SessionID\n65: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n66: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n67: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n68: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n69: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates ExpiresAt\n72: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n73: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n74: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n75: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating expiresAt is zero\n76: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox uses atomic DoMulti\n79: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Now().Add(time.Hour)`\n80: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n81: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n82: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a single `DoMulti` call:\n83:   - `SETNX session:sess-1 {json}` using `B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Nx().Build()`\n84:   - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} sess-1` using `B().Zadd().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix()), sandbox.SessionID).Build()`\n85:   - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} sess-1` using `B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(now), sandbox.SessionID).Build()`\n86: - **AND** all commands SHALL succeed for the operation to complete\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox fails if session already exists\n89: - **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` already exists\n90: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n91: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called with same SessionID\n92: - **THEN** `SETNX` SHALL indicate key exists (return value other than \"OK\")\n93: - **AND** the implementation SHALL return error indicating session already exists\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox requires existing key\n96: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n97: - **AND** key `session:sess-1` does NOT exist in Valkey\n98: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n99: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n100: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX` using `B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Xx().Build()`\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 302. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-014  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Base Spec:** [session-store/spec.md](../../session-store/spec.md)\n\nThe Valkey Storage Implementation provides a concrete Store implementation using Valkey as the backend. Valkey is a Redis-compatible storage engine, and this AR leverages the `valkey-go` client library to provide CRUD operations on sandbox information with sorted set indexes for expiry and last activity times.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Valkey Store Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Valkey-backed Store implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` that satisfies the Store interface.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775869093668,"end":1775869093688}}}}
