{"type":"text","timestamp":1775869108470,"sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0c014b001zYF6HkSMF6JAU0","messageID":"msg_d7a0be76b001x8kh9hOn5ncu8V","sessionID":"ses_285f75901ffeIBkgt46cBvDW9m","type":"text","text":"The delta-spec.md has been successfully written. Here's a summary of what was created:\n\n## Summary\n\n**File created:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md`\n\nThe delta specification for AR-014 (Valkey Storage Implementation) includes:\n\n### Requirements with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios:\n\n1. **Valkey Store Implementation** - 19 scenarios covering:\n   - `Ping` connectivity checks\n   - `GetSandboxBySessionID` retrieval with ErrNotFound handling\n   - `StoreSandbox` with validation and atomic DoMulti operations\n   - `UpdateSandbox` with XX flag semantics\n   - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` with cleanup\n   - `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` with ZRANGEBYSCORE\n   - `UpdateSessionLastActivity` with existence check\n   - `Close` connection cleanup\n   - `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` orphaned entry tolerance\n\n2. **Valkey Configuration** - 6 scenarios covering:\n   - Required VALKEY_ADDR\n   - Multiple address support\n   - Password requirements\n   - Optional DisableCache and ForceSingleClient flags\n   - Case-insensitive parsing\n\n3. **Provider Selection** - 3 scenarios covering:\n   - Default to Redis when STORE_TYPE unset\n   - Valkey selection\n   - Unsupported store type rejection\n\n### Additional sections:\n- Environment variables table\n- Dependencies (`github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`)\n- Implementation notes comparing Redis vs Valkey client patterns\n- Key differences table showing API variations\n\nAll existing tests pass (19 test cases in the store package).","time":{"start":1775869108467,"end":1775869108467}}}
